"Customer Information" shall mean any data or information which relates to an individual or any other person (including but not limited to the Bank staff and customers) or which is held by or is under the control of any member of the Bank. Customer Information shall further include any of the following information when collected or accessed (whether given by a Bank staff/ customer/ the Bank/ any person authorised by a Bank customer, obtained by the Merchant from any third party or system generated/ accessed/ collected or otherwise or whether accessed by the Merchant or on its behalf during provision of any Services to the Bank pursuant to this Agreement) in the process of or pursuant to provision of any Services provided by the Merchant, disclosed/shared by or on behalf of the Bank to the Merchant and the Merchant shall as the receiving party therefor be obligated to observe all the obligations under the confidentiality related provisions under this Agreement and be liable thereunder:
Personal information; and/or
Sensitive personal data or information.
‘Personal information’ shall mean any information, which either directly or indirectly, in combination with other information available or likely to be available with a body corporate or received from any third-party provider and is capable of identifying such person including but not limited to his/her name, age, gender, address, email address, telephone/ mobile number etc. 
‘Sensitive personal data or information” shall mean such personal information which consists of information relating to:
Password;
Contacts;
Data scraped/ collated/ gathered from other third party websites visited;
Financial information or account related information including but not limited bank account details or credit card or debit card or other payment instrument details;
Educational qualifications; 
Work Credentials; 
Employment details;
Income details;
Records and history; 
Biometric information;
Physical, physiological and mental health condition;
Sexual orientation;
Medical records and history; 
Any other type of information as may be specified by the Bank from time to time;
Any other information/ type of information which would be covered under the “sensitive personal data or information” under Applicable Law from time to time.

The Merchant shall (and shall ensure that its employees, agents and subcontractors shall) be required to maintain such administrative, technical and physical safeguards, and such processes, procedures and checks, to secure the Customer Information, as may be required under Applicable Law and/or industry standards or regulations issued by any Governmental Authority, which safeguards must be at least equal to or better than (a) the safeguards it currently has in place to protect its own data; and (b) generally accepted security standards in the financial service industry.
The administrative, technical and physical safeguards, processes, procedures and checks as provided for in this Clause I (Data Security) will be designed to: 
protect the security and confidentiality of the Customer Information in the Merchant’s possession;
ensure against any anticipated threats or hazards to the security and confidentiality of the Customer Information; 
protect against unauthorised access to or use of the Customer Information or associated records which could result in substantial harm or inconvenience to the Bank; and 
ensure the proper and secure disposal of such data. 
Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, the Merchant shall initiate all measures which a prudent organisation, in a similar situation, would take to secure and defend its systems that contain the Customer Information and/or which are utilised for the provision of the Services against “hackers” and others who may seek, without authorisation, to modify or access the Customer Information. The Merchant will periodically test its internal and external systems for potential areas where security could be breached.
The Merchant covenants that it shall take appropriate technical and organisational measures against (i) any unauthorised or unlawful processing or alteration of the Customer Information, at any point in time where the Customer Information is being received, processed, reviewed, stored or transferred by the Merchant, (ii) any resultant loss or destruction of, or damage to, the Customer Information due to unauthorised processing or alterations, and (iii) unauthorised or accidental access, processing, erasure, transfer, use, modification, disclosure, or other misuse of the Customer Information and shall ensure that only authorised personnel bound by adequate confidentiality obligations shall have access to the Customer Information and strictly on a ‘need to know’ basis strictly limited to the extent required to perform the Merchant’s obligations hereunder.
The Merchant shall (including its employees, agents and subcontractors) in respect of the Customer Information:
comply with any reasonable and commercially viable request made or direction given by any personnel of the Bank in connection with the requirements of any data protection laws; 
not do or permit anything to be done which might jeopardise or contravene the terms of any registration, notification or authorisation under any data protection laws; 
not to process any data (including personal or private information of personnel, clients or customers of the Bank), as part of maintenance unless it is acting on the express instructions of the Bank, and such data shall be treated as Confidential Information, for the purpose of this Agreement; 
use the Customer Information only for the purposes of fulfilling its obligations under this Agreement and to comply with instructions given by the Bank from time to time in connection with use of such data and records, and not retain the data and records for any longer than is necessary for these purposes;
not transfer Customer Information which is in the possession of the Merchant, outside India, or allow persons outside India to have access to it, without the prior written approval of the Bank; 
take all reasonable steps to ensure the reliability of the personnel which will have access to the Customer Information and ensure that the personnel of the Merchant, who access the Customer Information give a written undertaking not to access, use, disclose or retain the Customer Information except in performing its duties of employment and is informed that failure to comply with this undertaking may be a criminal offence and may also lead the Bank, the Merchant to take disciplinary action against the employee; 
observe the provisions of, and comply with any request made or direction given by the Bank in connection with any data protection laws; and
consider all suggestions by the Bank to ensure that the level of protection provided for the Customer Information is in accordance with this Agreement including making such changes as may be suggested by the Bank, if any at its own cost.
The Merchant must ensure that the Customer Information in the possession of the Merchant is not comingled with any other data including any data of its other customers or clients.
The Merchant acknowledges that any unauthorized access, destruction, alteration, addition or impediment to access or use of the data when stored in any computer, or the publication or communication or any document or any part thereof, by any person to whose knowledge or into whose possession or custody such data has come into (other than such persons to whom the Merchant is authorized to publish or disclose the document or any part thereof), may be a criminal offence; 
The Merchant shall indemnify the Bank and keep the Bank fully and effectively indemnified on demand, in respect of any type of liability, loss, damage, claim, demand, action, charge, cost (including legal/attorney fees), expenses and Taxes from time to time incurred by the Bank arising out of or in connection with any wrongful disclosure or misuse of data as a result of breach of this Clause I (Data Security).
Where the introduction, imposition or variation of any law, order or regulation or official directive or any change in the interpretation or application thereof by any competent authority makes it apparent that it is unlawful or impractical without breaching such law, order or regulation or official directive for the Merchant to give effect to its obligations under this Agreement, then notwithstanding anything herein to the contrary, the Merchant shall immediately consult the Bank to agree on any revision of the terms and conditions of this Agreement reasonably required in view of such circumstances.  
The Merchant agrees that it will not disclose, use, lecture upon or publish any of the Bank’s Confidential Information, except as such disclosure, use or publication may be required in connection with its work on a "need-to know" basis or unless the Bank expressly authorizes such disclosure in writing. The Merchant recognizes that all information created / accessed / processed by it, shall remain the sole property of the Bank and shall be returned to the Bank upon termination of this Agreement. 
The Merchant agrees to be vigilant and to report any breach of this Clause I (Data Security), all violations of information security, any breaches in the security practices, control processes and checks of the Merchant and all suspected security events immediately to (a) the Bank’s Information Security Group at security.incident@hdfcbank.com and (b) the concerned representatives and employees of the Bank which interact with the Merchant on a regular basis in respect of the Services of such violation.
The Merchant further confirms and agrees that it shall at all times during the continuance of this Agreement:
comply with the provisions of the Information Technology Act, 2000 and the applicable rules thereunder including without limitation the Information Technology (Reasonable security practices and procedures and sensitive personal data or information) Rules, 2011;
comply with all notifications, guidelines, circulars, issued by the RBI, in relation to securing card transactions; and
monitor the security practices, control processes and checks in respect of any Customer Information and other Confidential Information received by the Merchant, on a regular basis.
The Merchant shall ensure complete security of all information in relation to the Services and shall be responsible therefor at all times when the people, processes, and decision making authority required to secure such information as well as the information itself are in its control and: 
the Customer Information is stored whether permanently or temporarily on the systems of the Merchant or any of its agents, sub-contractors or representatives;
the Customer Information is being transferred from the systems of the Merchant or the systems of the Bank to the systems of the Merchant or of the Bank; and
the Customer Information is being transferred from the systems of the Merchant to the Bank, any other issuing bank, or any other person or in any other manner, during the course of provision of the Services under this Agreement.
The Merchant shall liable for any breach of security, compromise, theft, modification and/or corruption of the Customer Information which occurs at the times specified in this sub-clause 13 Error! Reference source not found. (Data Security), sub-clause 13 Error! Reference source not found. (Data Security) or sub-clause 13 Error! Reference source not found. (Data Security) above (“Data Compromise Events”), if the Data Compromise Event is the direct or indirect result of any act or omission of the Merchant. The Merchant hereby indemnifies and agrees to keep indemnified the Bank against any and all losses, damages, costs, expenses, fines, penalties, claims and Taxes from time to time which may be suffered or incurred by the Bank as a result of the Data Compromise Events.
The Merchant confirms that it has read and understood the “acceptable usage policy” posted on the information portal under the heading “information security group” of the Bank with respect to Services being provided onsite and/or offsite location, and agrees to protect the systems of the Bank and comply with the said policy. 
The Merchant confirms and agrees that the contents of this Agreement shall not be disclosed by the Merchant in whole or in part to any person other than the representatives/employees of the Merchant provided that the Merchant requires its representatives/employees to be bound by the terms of this Clause I (Data Security) to the fullest extent and the Merchant shall be responsible for any breach of confidentiality contemplated herein by any of its representatives/employees.

Definitions
The following terms when' used in this Agreement shall have the following meanings:
"Agreement" means this Agreement, including all Schedules, Annexures, Exihibits, Addendums, Amendments, SOWs and Change Orders executed pursuant hereto and annexure, supplements, appendices, and modifications thereof
"Confidential Information" means any and all information provided/made available by a Party ("Disclosing Party") to the other Party ("Receiving Party") or to which Receiving Party is privy, in written, representational, electronic, verbal or other form relating directly or indirectly to the present or potential business, operations or financial condition of or relating to the Disclosing Party including, but not limited to, information identified as being proprietary and/or confidential or pertaining to assets, liabilities, franchises, associates, employees, regulatory matters, litigation, pricing, billing methods, receivables, marketing plans or strategy, sales volumes, inventories, services rendered, customers, suppliers, financial or technical or service matters or data, Intellectual Property, software (including, without limitation, code, machine code, source code, related documentation, graphics, images, designs, logos, programs, layouts and specifications), hardware, technology, networks and any information which might reasonably be presumed to be proprietary or confidential in nature excluding any such information which: 
is known to the public (through no act or omission of the Receiving Party in violation of this Agreement); or 
is lawfully acquired by the Receiving Party from an independent source having no obligation to maintain the confidentiality of such information; or
was known to the Receiving Party prior to its disclosure under this Agreement; 
the Receiving Party can prove that it was or is independently developed by the Receiving Party without breach of this Agreement; or 
is required to be disclosed by governmental or judicial order, in which case the Receiving Party shall give the Disclosing Party prompt written notice, where possible, and use reasonable efforts to ensure that such disclosure is accorded confidential treatment.
"Effective Date" means …….18th March, 2020.
"Intellectual Property Rights" or “IPR” means:
all inventions (whether patentable or un-patentable and whether or not reduced to practice), all improvements thereto, and all patents, patent applications, and patent disclosures, together with all re-issuances, continuations, continuations-in-part, revisions, extensions and re-examinations thereof;
all trademarks, service marks, logos, trade names and corporate names, together with all translations, adaptations, derivations and combinations thereof, including all goodwill associated therewith and all applications, registrations and renewals in connection therewith and also rights in design, model;
all copyrightable works, all copyrights and all applications, registrations and renewals in connection therewith;
all mask works and all applications, registrations and renewals in connection therewith;
all computer software (including data and related documentation), code, machine code, source code, related documentation, graphics, images, designs, logos, programs, layouts and specifications;
all other proprietary rights of whatsoever description whether or not protected and whether or not capable of protection, and
all copies and tangible embodiments thereof regardless of form and medium.
"Program" means the software products developed as a result of the Services provided by Service Provider under a SOW and this Agreement, to Client and any, updates, upgrades, customizations, derivatives to such software products.
"Services" means any services, deliverables, Program to be provided or rendered by Service Provider pursuant to respective SOW”.
"Statement of Work" or "SOW" means each mutually agreed scope of work document, describing the desired Services and if applicable any additional terms and conditions pursuant to which Service Provider shall perform such Services.
"Term" shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause 4 below.
Interpretation
Save where the context otherwise requires in this Agreement:
Words importing persons or parties shall include firms and corporations and any organization having legal capacity.
Words importing the singular include the plural and vice versa where the context so requires.
References to any law shall include such law as from time to time enacted, amended, supplemented or re-enacted;
Reference to any gender includes a reference to all other genders;
References to the words "include" or "including" shall be construed without limitation;
References to this Agreement or any other agreement, deed or other instrument or document shall be construed as a reference to such agreement, deed or other instrument or document as the same may from time to time be amended, varied, supplemented or novated;
The headings and titles in this Agreement are indicative and shall not be deemed part thereof or be taken into consideration in the interpretation or construction of the Agreement.
Recitals of this Agreement shall be considered as an operative part of this Agreement.

This Agreement shall come into force on the Effective Date and shall continue for a period of 2 years (“Term”) unless terminated as per below clauses.
Either Party ("Non-Defaulting Party") may terminate this Agreement and/or any SOW in the event of a material breach of the Agreement or a SOW by the other Party ("Defaulting Party") provided that such breach is not cured within 30 days of the Defaulting Party receiving a written notice in this behalf from the Non-Defaulting Party. For the avoidance of doubt, it is clarified that this Agreement shall survive the termination of the Agreement solely to support the SOW till expiry or termination of the said SOW.
Client shall have the right to terminate the Agreement and/or respective SOW, if the services provided by the resources are not as per the requirements of Client with a notice of 30 days for the termination of the Agreement.
Client shall have the right to terminate any resource of Service Provider by serving 30 days prior notice
Client shall be entitled to terminate this Agreement and/or any or all the SOWs immediately and forthwith in the event of breach by Service Provider and/or its personnel and/or its sub-contractors and/or its agents and/or its representatives of the following:
code of conduct of Client (including Client’s policies); 
any applicable laws to Service Provider and Client including but not limited to laws related to prevention of sexual harassment;
any misconduct;
charges of any offence involving moral turpitude;
breach of confidentiality.
Client may terminate the Agreement and/or any or all SOWs with 30 days’ notice to Service Provider in following events:
If Service Provider disposes of the whole or any substantial part of its assets, operations or business other than in the normal course of business;
any step is taken to enter into any arrangement between Service provider and its creditors;
Service Provider ceases to be able to pay its debts as they become due; 
Service provider ceases to carry on business;
any step is taken by a mortgagee to enter into possession or dispose of the whole or any part of Service Provider’s assets or business; 
any step is taken to appoint a receiver, a receiver and manager, a trustee in bankruptcy, a liquidator, a provisional liquidator, an administrator or other like person of the whole or any part of Service Provider’s assets or business;
there is any change in the direct or indirect beneficial ownership or control of Service Provider
for convenience without assigning any reason and without any liability. 
In the event of any termination of this Agreement or a SOW, save as required to enforce clause 6 (Ownership of Intellectual Property), each Party shall return to the other Party any material relating to the other Party and, if third party software components are involved, any material relating to such third party within a period of seven days of effective termination..
The provisions of this Agreement, which are intended to survive from termination, such as confidentiality, indemnification, arbitration etc. shall continue to bind the Parties.

The Parties hereby represent and warrant that:
Each of them has full power and authority to carryon its business;
The execution and delivery of this Agreement will not result in breach of any terms and conditions, or constitute default under the applicable laws or any contractual obligations to which it is bound or violate any rule, regulation or law of any Government or any order, judgement or decree of any court or government body, its Memorandum and Articles of Association;
The execution and delivery of this Agreement has been duly authorised by all necessary Board of Directors and/or shareholder's actions;
Service Provider represents, warrants and covenants as a condition precedent to this Agreement that:
it has the authority and the right to enter into this Agreement and each SOW, to perform Services and provide deliverables under this Agreement, and under each SOW.
each of its employees, agents and subcontractors assigned on any project under a SOW has the proper skill, training and background necessary to accomplish their assigned tasks
all Services will be performed in a competent and professional manner, by qualified personnel and if specified in respective SOW will conform to parameters/service levels and acceptance criteria as specified in that SOW;
it has complied with, and will continue to comply with, all applicable domestic, foreign and local laws and regulations and, shall obtain all applicable permits and licenses in connection with its obligations under this Agreement;
Service Provider has not and shall not insert any code which would have the effect of disabling or otherwise shutting down all or any portion of any Services/ deliverable provided hereunder;
Service Provider shall ensure that no viruses or similar items are coded or introduced in any Services/ deliverables and shall expeditiously incorporate, install and make available all security patches, bug fixes and/or modifications required to render the deliverables free from security risks;
If the Services as per respective SOW includes delivery/development of any software, such software shall comply with all specification of such software and requirements of Client and  Service Provider shall promptly correct and repair, at no cost to Client, any defect, malfunction or non-conformity that prevents such software from conforming and performing as warranted;
Service Provider shall be responsible for the verification and background check of its personnel.
If the Services as per respective SOW involves deputation of any personnel/resource by Service Provider, in addition to other terms mentioned herein following also shall be applicable:
Such resource shall at all times be considered as employees of Service Provider and not of Client and Service Provider shall be responsible to comply with all the applicable labour laws and shall defend, hold harmless and keep indemnified the Client in that respect;
Service Provider shall ensure that its personnel shall comply with all the policies of Client;
Service Provider shall ensure that none of its resource is engaged in any misconduct and shall be replaced immediately in the event of any commission of misconduct as determined by Client in its absolute discretion;
Service Provider shall ensure that none of its resource is facing the charges of any offence involving moral turpitude;
;
Service Provider shall provide resource to Client for short duration of 1-6 months to meet Client’s requirement;
If existing resource resigns, Service Provider shall provide replacement to Client within 2 weeks;
In case, there is no show from selected resource on joining day then Service Provider shall provide the replacement to Client within 1 week;
In case, resource absconds or discontinuous the employment within 1 month from joining date, Service Provider shall not raise invoice for the respective resource. However, if the Client terminates the service of the resource, the fee shall be paid till the last working day of such resource.;

The resource deployed shall work as per instructions of Client however, under the guidance and supervision of the Service Provider;
Client’s holiday calendar will be followed by all contract resources. Resources will be allowed to take 1 day leave per month. Any unclaimed leave will not be carried forward to the subsequent month(s) or eligible for encashment. Excess leave taken during the month will be deducted from the payments to Service Provider.

The Service Provider represents and warrants to and for ICICI Bank's benefit as follows (which representations and warranties shall be deemed repeated by the Service Provider everyday):
