clauses.original_text:
Definitions
“Applicable Laws” means any applicable laws, statutes, code, rules and regulations including RBI rules, circulars and regulations, Information Technology Act and regulations, privacy laws and regulations, Anti Bribery laws and regulations,  orders, injunctions, judgement, decree, ruling, import-export restrictions/regulations, any decision, license or authorization having the force of law in relation to the business of a Party issued by legal/regulatory authority, or any legally obligatory lawful requirement or demand of any Government Authority, Bank policies and any amendments to such laws, regulations etc.; 
“Confidential Information” has the meaning ascribed to such term in Clause 9;
“Government Authority” means (a) central, state, local, municipal, or other government; (b) governmental or quasi-governmental authority of any nature (including any governmental division, subdivision, department, agency, bureau, branch, office, commission, council, board, instrumentality, officer, official, representative, organization and any court or other tribunal); (c)   applicable legal authorities (d) applicable regulatory authorities;
“Intellectual Property” “ shall mean all intellectual property of the Bank and includes without limitation all of Bank’s patents, trademarks, logos, permits, service marks, brands, trade names, trade secrets, proprietary information and knowledge, technology, computer programs, databases, copyrights, licenses, software, franchises, formulae, designs, Confidential Information and all other intellectual property and all the information, documents, software, codes and/or any  product/services/software etc. developed by the Service Provider for the Bank; 
“Services” has the meaning ascribed to such term in Clause 3.1;
“Service Fee” has the meaning ascribed to such term in Clause 4.1; and 
“Term” has the meaning ascribed to such term in Clause 6.1.
Interpretation
In this Agreement, except where the context otherwise requires:
any reference herein to a Recital, Clause, Schedule is to such Recital, Clause or Schedule of this Agreement;
any reference to persons includes individuals, firms, partnerships, companies, corporations, associations, organizations, Competent Authorities, states, foundations and trusts (in each case whether or not having separate legal personality);
any reference to “including” or “include(s)” shall be construed as being by way of example and shall not limit or prejudice the generality of any preceding word or words; 
any reference to a statute or statutory provision shall include any modification or re-enactment thereof for the time being in force and shall include all instruments, orders, plans, registrations, permissions and directions for the time being made, issued or given thereunder or deriving validity therefrom;
references to the singular include the plural and vice versa; 
references to the gender includes all legally accepted genders;
any reference to any other document is a reference to that other document as amended, varied, supplemented, or novated (in each case, other than in breach of the provisions of this Agreement) at any time;
all schedules, annexures, documents, standards, guidelines, codes, etc. specified in terms of and for the fulfilment of this Agreement, shall form integral part of this Agreement;
the expression “this Clause” shall, unless followed by a reference to a specific provision, be deemed to refer to the whole Clause (not merely the sub-clause, paragraph or other provision) in which the expression occurs;
the terms “herein”, “hereof”, “hereto”, “hereunder” and words of similar purport refer to this Agreement as a whole;
the headings are inserted for convenience only and shall not affect the construction of this Agreement;
where a word or phrase is defined, other parts of speech and grammatical forms and the cognate variations of that word or phrase shall have corresponding meanings; and
the rule of construction, if any, that a contract should be interpreted against the Party responsible for the drafting and preparation thereof, shall not apply.

Upon termination of this Agreement for any reason as stated in Clause 6, above, the Service Provider shall:
immediately discontinue the utilisation of any Intellectual Property of the Bank including but not limited to its logo, tradenames, trademarks and name and shall immediately hand over any and all information, and documentation including copies of such Intellectual Property to the Bank;
immediately return to the Bank or destroy as per the mandate of the Bank, Confidential Information, originals and copies of any and all materials/Confidential Information provided/comes in to possession of/generated during the Term of this Agreement to the Service Provider and/or its Representatives pursuant to this Agreement or in the course of provision of the Services, including any promotional and marketing materials in its possession; 
immediately handover to the Bank any and all software, systems and tangible and intangible assets developed by the Service Provider for the Bank which is including but not limited to codes, passwords, usernames, etc. The Service Provider shall also handover to the Bank the documentation in relation to any software and /or any other intellectual property developed for the Bank.  All such software, systems, information, codes, passwords, usernames etc. shall be intellectual property of the Bank;
The Service Provider shall immediately seize to provide the Services on the last day of the termination notice after due handover of the current proposals/customers etc. in the format as prescribed by the Bank within the notice period of the termination; 
The Service Provider shall confirm in writing to the Bank of having complied with the provisions of this Clause as and when requested by the Bank;
The Service Provider shall support the Bank, if so required by the Bank, with an additional cost for the period of 3 (three) months after termination of this Agreement for due migration of the Services to the another service provider;
If the Service Provider is having access to any of the software of the Bank, the Service Provider shall immediately stop using such software and handover all the passwords etc. in relation to the said software to the Bank; and 
The Service Provider shall ensure that if the Service Provider is using any of its equipment’s approved by the Bank for the purpose of this Agreement, the Service Provider shall ensure that there are suitable back to back arrangements between Service Provider and the original equipment manufacturers at its own cost.
The Bank shall be entitled to publish the termination of this Agreement if the same is mandated by applicable legal/regulatory authorities and/or it’s required under applicable laws/regulations. Further, no Service Fee shall be payable by the Bank from the effective date of termination, save those that are due and payable in respect of Services already rendered before the date of termination.

The Service Provider shall for itself and for the Representatives/sub-contractors/employees indemnify and agrees to keep indemnified and hold harmless (“Indemnifying Party”), the Bank (including its affiliates, subsidiaries group companies, holding companies, their respective employees, directors, agents, affiliates and representatives) (“Indemnified Party”) from and against any and all claims, costs, direct losses, damages, judgments, tax assessments, penalties, interest and expenses (including without limitation attorneys’ fees) arising out of and/or related to: 
any actual breach of terms and conditions,
any actual breach of Indemnifying Party’s representations, warranties, or obligations set forth in this Agreement; 
non-performance, deficiency in Services;
Breach of Confidentiality;
fraud, misrepresentations, gross negligence etc.
Neither Party shall be liable for any special, indirect, incidental, consequential or punitive damages, penalty for lost profits, lost revenue or lost opportunities, arising out of or in connection with this Agreement, even if that Party has been advised of (or knows or should know of) the possibility of such damages. 

The Bank shall have no liability whatsoever under this Agreement including for any loss or injury to any property or any individual assigned to perform the Services under this Agreement or otherwise, by the Service Provider while on premises of the Bank or anywhere else including any liability that may arise as a result of malfunction of any equipment or otherwise howsoever.

Aster shall indemnify, defend, and hold harmless Softcell, its officers, directors, employees, and agents from and against all claims, liabilities, losses, damages, costs, and expenses (including reasonable legal fees) arising from or in connection with:
;
Violation of any applicable laws or regulations by Aster;
Any act or omission of Aster, its employees, or agents resulting in personal injury, property damage, or third-party claims.

Confidential Information. As used in this Agreement, the term “Confidential Information” means any information disclosed by one Party to the other pursuant to this Agreement which is in written, graphic, machine readable or other tangible form and is marked “Confidential”, “Proprietary” or in some other manner to indicate its confidential nature. Confidential Information may also include oral information disclosed by one Party to the other pursuant to this Agreement, provided that such information is designated as confidential at the time of disclosure, or within a reasonable time (not to exceed thirty (30) days) after its first oral disclosure, and such writing is marked in a manner to indicate its confidential nature and delivered to the receiving Party.
Confidentiality. Each Party will treat as confidential all Confidential Information of the other Party and will use reasonable efforts not to disclose such Confidential Information to any third-party. Without limiting the foregoing, each of the Parties will use at least the same degree of care with respect to the Confidential Information that such Party uses to prevent the disclosure of its own confidential information of like importance. Each Party will promptly notify the other Party of any actual or suspected misuse or unauthorized disclosure of the other Party’s Confidential Information. 
For the purposes of this section, the Party disclosing Confidential Information shall be referred to as the “Disclosing Party” and the Party receiving the Confidential Information shall be referred to as the “Receiving Party”.
Exceptions. Notwithstanding the above, neither Party will have liability to the other with regard to any Confidential Information of the other with regard to any Confidential Information of the other which the receiving Party can demonstrate:
was in the public domain at the time it was disclosed or has become in the public domain through no fault of the Receiving Party;
was known to the Receiving Party, without restriction, at the time of disclosure, as evidenced by the Receiving Party’s files in existence at the time of disclosure;
is disclosed with the prior written approval of the Disclosing Party;
was independently developed by the Receiving Party without use or reliance upon Confidential Information of the Disclosing Party;
becomes known to the Receiving Party, without restriction, from a source other than the Disclosing Party without breach of this Agreement by the Receiving Party;
is disclosed by the Disclosing Party to any third-party without confidentiality obligations similar to those contained in this Agreement; or
is disclosed pursuant to the order or requirement of a court, administrative agency, or other governmental body, provided, however, that the Receiving Party will, to the extent lawful and reasonably possible, provide prompt notice thereof to the disclosing party to enable the disclosing party to seek a protective order or otherwise prevent or restrict such disclosure.
Confidentiality of Agreement. Each Party agrees that the specific terms and conditions of this Agreement will be treated as confidential information and that no disclosure thereof will be made in any form without the prior written consent of the other Party, except (i) as required by applicable disclosure laws; (ii) to accountants, banks, financing sources, lawyers and related Parties subject to a duty not to disclose to others; or (iii) in connection with the enforcement of this Agreement. The confidentiality obligations of the Parties hereunder shall survive for a period of three (3) years from the expiry or termination of this Agreement.

