The term of this Agreement will commence on the Effective Date and will remain in effect until terminated pursuant to this Agreement (“Term”). Any Notice of termination of this Agreement must include a termination date.
Termination for Cause: ICICI Bank may terminate this Agreement at any time without giving notice to the Service Provider, including without limitation, in the following events: 
The Service Provider is in breach of any of its representations or has committed any fraud, misconduct, omission or misrepresentation under the terms herein;
The Service Provider has become the subject matter of Sanctions;
The Service Provider commits any other breach of the terms of this Agreement and in case of a breach capable of being remedied, shall have failed, within  days after the receipt of a request in writing from ICICI Bank, to remedy the breach, (such request containing a notice of ICICI Bank’s intention to terminate).
The Service Provider breaches its obligations in respect of Intellectual Property Rights and/or ownership;
The Service Provider becomes the subject of a petition in bankruptcy or reorganization proceeding and such proceeding shall not have been dismissed or stayed within 30 (thirty) days after such filing.
Termination for Convenience: Notwithstanding anything contained herein, ICICI Bank reserves the right to terminate this Agreement with or without any cause by providing the Service Provider a prior notice of 7 (seven) days.
Termination due to Regulatory Non-Compliance: ICICI Bank shall have the right to terminate this Agreement in accordance with Clause 8.2.
Termination due to Change of Control: ICICI Bank shall have the right to terminate this Agreement in accordance with Clause 21.2.
Effect of Termination: The Parties agree that if the Agreement is terminated - 
as per Clause 22.2, Clause 22.4 or Clause 22.5, the Service Provider shall forthwith refund to ICICI Bank, the fees paid to the Service Provider hereunder;
the Service Provider shall return or delete (as instructed by ICICI Bank) all the Confidential Information of ICICI Bank, and give a certificate certifying such deletion upon the request of ICICI Bank;
the accrued rights of ICICI Bank and any provision hereof and shall remain in full force and effect and shall be enforceable against the Service Provider, notwithstanding such expiry or termination.
the Service Provider will cease using ICICI Bank Materials upon expiration or termination of the Agreement and shall forthwith return the same to ICICI Bank.

