The Bank is a leading and innovative co-operative sector bank, having more than 250 branches across India with a network of ATMs. The branches are automated through banking solutions. The Bank is also having internet banking, SMS banking, cards, depository services etc.;
Service Provider is engaged in the business of providing business-to-business IT infrastructure & services;
The Bank being desirous of engaging service provider for providing services as more particularly listed in Annexure A (hereinafter referred to as “Services”) from time to time as may be required by the Bank, the Bank had invited proposals;
Pursuant to examining number of proposals that the Bank had received, Bank had selected Service Provider to be responsible for rendering the Services;
Service Provider has represented to the Bank that Service Provider has sufficient knowledge, expertise, competency and appropriate human and other resources as required for rendering the Services;
Service Provider acknowledges that based on the above representations the Bank has selected the Service Provider for awarding the contract as per the term of this Agreement;
The Parties are desirous of recording the terms as agreed between the Parties, as set out hereinafter.
NOW, THEREFORE, FOR AND IN CONSIDERATION OF THE MUTUAL PROMISES AND COVENANTS HEREIN CONTAINED, THE PARTIES HERETO DO HEREBY AGREE AS FOLLOWS:
Definition and Interpretation
Definitions
When used in this Agreement (including the recitals), the following words and expressions shall have the meanings assigned hereto
“Acceptance Criteria” shall mean the criteria set out by the Bank which is required to be conformed by the Deliverables for the acceptance thereby by the Bank in a fixed price Work Order;
“Acceptance Period” shall mean seven (7) working days from the date on which the Deliverables are delivered to the Bank;
“Acceptance Testing” shall mean the testing of Deliverables as per Cl. 3.1.4 of the Agreement to ascertain if the Deliverables are in accordance with the Acceptance Criteria;
“Affiliate” shall mean, in relation to any Party, a person who controls, is controlled by, or is under the common control with such Party. For the purposes of this definition, “control” means with respect to a person which is a company or corporation, the ownership, directly or indirectly, of more than 50% (fifty percent) of the voting shares of such person, and with respect to a person which is not a company or corporation, the power to direct the management and policies of such person, whether by operation of law or by contract or otherwise;
“Agreement” means this Agreement and any and all schedules, recitals, annexure and exhibits which are attached to it or incorporated in it by reference and also includes any Work Orders extension/s addendum/s and/or amendment/s if any to this Agreement; 
“Applicable Law” shall mean any statute, law, regulation, ordinance, rule, judgment, order, decree, by-law, clearance, directive, guideline, policy, requirement, other governmental restrictions or any other similar form of decision of, or determination or any interpretation or administration having the force of law or any of the foregoing, by any court or any Government Authority having jurisdiction over the matter in question in India and applicable to the Parties herein, whether in effect as of the date of this Agreement or thereafter;
“Bank Software” and “Bank Hardware” shall mean the software and or hardware provided by or through the Bank;
“Business Day" shall mean a day other than: (i) public holidays on which Bank is closed; and (ii) a day on which normal banking business cannot be transacted;
“Change Order” shall mean a request for any alteration, change or modification to the Services, as mutually agreed in writing as per Cl. 16.19;
“Control” (including with correlative meaning, the terms “Controlling”, “Controlled by” and “under common Control with”) in relation to a Person shall mean:
the acquisition or control of more than 50% (fifty per cent) of the voting rights / interest or of the issued share capital of such Person (on a fully diluted basis); or
the right to appoint and/or remove all or the majority of the members of such Person’s board or other governing body; or 
having powers to direct the management or policy decisions of such Person, whether obtained directly or indirectly, and whether obtained by ownership of share capital, the possession of voting rights / interest or by contract
“Confidential Information” means and includes all information of whatever nature used in or otherwise made available by the Bank and/ or  its Affiliates, including information which is disclosed in any tangible form and is clearly labelled or marked as confidential / proprietary or it’s equivalent, or all information concerning provided by the Bank and/or its Affiliates  that is not known or generally available to the public at large, including without limitation, data, Source code, software and documentation, existing systems and computer software, future projects, business development or planning, commercial relationships and negotiations, the marketing of goods or services (including customer names and lists, sales targets, statistics,) financial statements and other financial information, employees lists, salaries and benefits and all other data sent by the Bank and/or its Affiliates whether written, oral or on magnetic or other media exchanged to between the Parties, on or after the date hereof., is nevertheless disclosed as a result of the Parties' discussions and based on legends or other markings, the circumstances of disclosure or the nature of the information itself, should reasonably be understood by the Service Provider as being proprietary and/ or confidential to the Bank and/or its Affiliates. Confidential Information shall however, exclude any information which (i) is/ was publicly known or comes into public domain; (ii) is received by the receiving Party from a third party, without breach of this Agreement; (iii) was already in the possession of receiving Party, without confidentiality restrictions, at the time of disclosure by the disclosing Party; (iv) is permitted for disclosure by the disclosing Party in writing; (v) independently developed by the receiving party without use of Confidential Information; (vi) is required to be disclosed by the receiving Party pursuant to any order or requirement from court, administrative or governmental agency, provided that the receiving Party shall give the disclosing Party prompt written notice of such order or requirement and an opportunity to contest or seek an appropriate protective order.
“Delivery” means supply of Deliverable(s) at the Bank’s designated location;
“Deliverables” means solution, software, material or item developed by the Service Provider and or its Qualified Personnel for the Bank as may be specified in Work Order, including any specifications, design documents, documentation, manuals, process descriptions, reports, products, software, codes, drawings, and data and databases;
“Effective Date” means the date of execution of this Agreement from which date this Agreement and the obligations hereunder shall come into effect between the Parties;
“Fees” shall mean the fees payable, and expenses incurred for the Services and Deliverable by the Bank and more particularly described under the Work Order.
Event of “Force Majeure” shall mean act of God including but not limited to fire, flood, earthquake, windstorm or other natural disaster, act of any sovereign including bit not limited to war, invasion, act of foreign enemies, hostilities, whether war be declared or not, civil war, rebellion, strike, government actions, insurrection, any type of epidemics and/or pandemics  being beyond the control of any of the Parties and affecting performance of this Agreement;
“Intellectual Property” includes all patents, trademarks, business processes, source code, domain names, works of authorship, designs, utility models, copyrights, whether registered or unregistered, including, but not limited to moral rights and any similar rights in any country, whether negotiable or not, and also includes any applications for any of the foregoing and the right to apply for them in any part of the world; and all ideas, concepts, processes, inventions, creations, discoveries, programs, codes, software, algorithms, databases, Trade Secrets, know-how, improvements upon, additions or any research efforts relating to any of the above, whether registrable or not, and any correspondence or documents relating to any of the above;
“Intellectual Property Rights (IPR)” means all current and future copyright, patents, trademarks or rights in databases, inventions or trade secrets, know-how, rights in designs, topographies, trade and business names, domain names, marks and devices (whether or not registered) and all other intellectual property rights and applications for any of those rights (where such applications can be made) capable of protection in any relevant country of the world;Malicious Code” means “any computer code or any other procedures, routines or mechanisms  including any time bomb, virus, software lock, access codes, trojan horse, drop-dead device, worm, malicious logic or trap door which may: (a) disrupt, disable, harm or impair in any material way an IT System’s operation, (b) cause such IT System to damage or corrupt any data, storage media, programs, equipment or communications of the Company, its Subsidiaries, or their clients, or otherwise interfere with the Company and its Subsidiaries’ operations; or (c) permit any third party to access any such IT Systems to cause disruption, disablement, harm, impairment, damage erasure or corruption”.
“Non Disclosure Agreement” means the agreement to be entered into between the Service Provider and each of Service Provider’s Employee/Qualified Personnel or any Third Party which may be privy to the Confidential Information, in a form to be approved in writing by the Bank;
“Person” shall unless specifically provided otherwise, mean any individual, body corporate, corporation, partnership, joint venture, trust or Government Authority as the context may admit
“Project Sites” means the branches of the Bank along with the administrative offices/Data Centre/Disaster Recovery Centre or any other location, as specified by the Bank in the Work Order;
“Qualified Personnel” means full-time employees of Service Provider or personnel of Original Equipment Manufacturer (OEM) or consultants whose professional credentials meet the requirements outlined by the Bank in the relevant Work Order, and have been accepted for deployment in respect of the Work Order by the Bank;
“Services” means the services to be provided by the Service Provider to the Bank from time to time in accordance with the Work Order(s), including other support functions as provided by the Service Provider in accordance with the provisions of this Agreement;
Services Provider’s Employees” means all the employees of the Service Provider and shall include any Qualified Personnel and employee or staff who has access to information provided by the Bank for the purpose of provision of service by the Service Provider;
“Third Party” means any Person who is not a party to this Agreement;
“Work Order(s)” or “Purchase Order” or “Service Order” means a work order issued by the Bank from time to time specifying details of the scope of work, details of project, the work to be performed, the nature of professional services required, Deliverables, the Project Site, the fees to be paid to Service Provider and other relevant information such as service levels, Service Provider’s Employee(ies)/Qualified Personnel qualifications, which is accepted by the Service Provider in writing and includes any Schedule, Exhibit or Appendices to such work order, whether now existing or subsequently executed by the Parties. 
Interpretation
In this Agreement, the headings are used for convenience and ease of reference and are not to be construed in the construction or interpretation of any provision of this Agreement. 
